headline: Why Is Ingersoll Rand (IR) Stock Rocketing Higher Today

headline: IR Q4 Deep Dive: Recurring Revenue and M&A Drive Growth Amid Margin Pressures
summary: Industrial manufacturing company Ingersoll Rand (NYSE:IR) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 10.1% year on year to $2.09 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.96 per share was 6.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
